                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Great Britain/c: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-15T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>167. Reference Department’s circular, through Paris, dated June 3, 10 a.m.,
                    regarding World War Foreign Debt Commission. It is the desire of the Commission
                    to begin discussions with the British Government at the earliest possible date.
                    You should, therefore, take the first opportunity to express informally to the
                    Foreign Office the hope that the British Government may see its way to name the
                    British representative at an early date and that it may be possible to proceed
                    with the negotiations without delay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
